I'm sorry.

94
00:04:23,812 --> 00:04:24,812
I'm sorry.

95
00:04:24,812 --> 00:04:25,812
I'm sorry.

96
00:04:25,812 --> 00:04:26,802
I'm sorry.

97
00:04:26,802 --> 00:04:44,802
You walked around with the two boys and you forgot me here. I know that it's
more fun than sitting here with me. I find it boring too. But you could have
come over to me. After all, I can't come to you.

98
00:04:48,924 --> 00:04:50,924
But Clara...

99
00:04:57,924 --> 00:05:01,924
I'm sorry Clara, but I thought you wanted to see the butterfly.

100
00:05:01,924 --> 00:05:04,924
I know. It wasn't right what I said.

101
00:05:04,924 --> 00:05:07,924
What can you do about me being sick?

102
00:05:07,924 --> 00:05:08,924
Clara...

103
00:05:08,924 --> 00:05:10,924
No, let me go. I want to be alone.

104
00:05:10,924 --> 00:05:14,924
I was alone all my life. Go and play with the other children.

105
00:05:14,924 --> 00:05:16,924
But Clara...

106
00:05:17,634 --> 00:05:19,634
What is it?

107
00:05:19,634 --> 00:05:23,634
Children, children, where have you been so long?

108
00:05:23,634 --> 00:05:26,634
We have already prepared the food.

109
00:05:26,634 --> 00:05:29,634
Oh, isn't it wonderful out here?

110
00:05:29,634 --> 00:05:31,634
There are greens and flowers everywhere.

111
00:05:31,634 --> 00:05:33,634
And there are flowers in all colors.

112
00:05:33,634 --> 00:05:35,634
Clara, look!

113
00:05:37,634 --> 00:05:39,548
Clara?

114
00:05:39,548 --> 00:05:43,788
Oh, tell me, my dear, are these tears?

115
00:05:43,788 --> 00:05:46,268
We would cry on such a beautiful day.

116
00:05:46,268 --> 00:05:48,348
Grandmother, please tell Mrs. Rottenmeier

117
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,468
she should send Heidi back home to the mountains.

118
00:05:50,468 --> 00:05:53,828
Oh, but child!

119
00:05:53,828 --> 00:05:56,348
I don't want to see her anymore. She should go.

120
00:05:56,348 --> 00:05:59,748
I'm afraid I just don't know what you mean.

121
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:01,870
I know what she's thinking, Grandmother.

122
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:05,870
I ran away with two strangers because I wanted to catch a butterfly for her.

123
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:07,870
And I left her alone.

124
00:06:07,870 --> 00:06:09,870
I've done everything wrong again.

125
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:13,870
And that's supposed to be all that Heidi has done wrong?

126
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:15,870
What kind of child are you?

127
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:18,870
I don't care. I want to go home anyway.

128
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:20,870
Johan is supposed to finish the cart.

129
00:06:20,870 --> 00:06:22,870
But we just arrived here.

130
00:06:22,870 --> 00:06:25,870
You want to go home so quickly?

131
00:06:25,892 --> 00:06:27,392
Do you mean that seriously?

132
00:06:27,392 --> 00:06:28,892
Yes, I mean that seriously.

133
00:06:28,892 --> 00:06:30,192
What a pity for you.

134
00:06:30,192 --> 00:06:31,892
We can't go yet.

135
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:33,892
And do you know why? I don't feel like it.

136
00:06:33,892 --> 00:06:35,692
And you? Do you want to go home already?

137
00:06:35,692 --> 00:06:37,592
I'd like to stay.

138
00:06:37,592 --> 00:06:39,092
But if Clara really wants to...

139
00:06:39,092 --> 00:06:42,592
Ah, so you like the city with Miss Rottenmeier better.

140
00:06:42,592 --> 00:06:44,692
You'd rather do homework.

141
00:06:44,692 --> 00:06:46,192
I understand.

142
00:06:48,892 --> 00:06:51,392
We have strawberry jam with us.

143
00:06:53,822 --> 00:06:57,822
If Clara really wants to go home, then I want to too.

144
00:06:57,822 --> 00:06:58,822
That's better.

145
00:06:58,822 --> 00:06:59,822
You think?

146
00:06:59,822 --> 00:07:01,822
I'll tell Johann. He's supposed to tie the horses.

147
00:07:01,822 --> 00:07:02,822
Heidi, but...

148
00:07:02,822 --> 00:07:04,822
So, and now to you.

149
00:07:04,822 --> 00:07:06,822
You want us to send Heidi away.

150
00:07:06,822 --> 00:07:08,822
So you want to be alone again.

151
00:07:10,822 --> 00:07:12,822
So she's equal to you all of a sudden.

152
00:07:14,822 --> 00:07:17,822
And I always thought you loved her.

153
00:07:18,822 --> 00:07:20,822
Heidi...

154
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:25,710
Heidi, come back!

155
00:07:29,710 --> 00:07:32,710
Leave it with the cart. I'd like to stay here.

156
00:07:35,710 --> 00:07:37,710
Or do you not want to anymore?

157
00:07:38,710 --> 00:07:40,710
Come here to me, Heidi.

158
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:42,710
Clara noticed that everything was nonsense.

159
00:07:42,710 --> 00:07:44,710
Yes? Did she?

160
00:07:44,710 --> 00:07:46,710
Now say something nice to her, Clara.

161
00:07:46,710 --> 00:07:48,710
She is such a sweet little thing and I really like her.

162
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:50,710
Should I catch another butterfly?

163
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:52,564
No.

164
00:07:52,564 --> 00:07:56,964
Then all the problems seem to be solved now. Except for one, of course, the most
important thing.

165
00:07:56,964 --> 00:07:59,764
I wonder all the time if you've never been hungry.

166
00:08:01,364 --> 00:08:02,464
That looks pretty.

167
00:08:02,464 --> 00:08:03,964
You think I like something like that?

168
00:08:04,564 --> 00:08:05,764
You like it very much.

169
00:08:07,364 --> 00:08:08,964
May I take the flower pot with me?

170
00:08:11,964 --> 00:08:12,764
Clara!

171
00:08:15,326 --> 00:08:17,326
Oh, a butterfly, Clara.

172
00:08:17,326 --> 00:08:19,326
Psst, I'll catch it for you.

173
00:08:19,326 --> 00:08:21,326
Then you can see it clearly.

174
00:08:21,326 --> 00:08:23,326
No, Heidi, please let it sit there. It looks like a loop.

175
00:08:23,326 --> 00:08:25,326
A living one.

176
00:08:25,326 --> 00:08:27,326
Come here, loop.

177
00:08:27,326 --> 00:08:29,326
It's like flying to its friend.

178
00:08:33,326 --> 00:08:35,326
Goodbye, butterfly.

179
00:08:35,326 --> 00:08:37,326
Now there are even three butterflies.

180
00:08:45,326 --> 00:08:47,326
The end

181
00:08:51,454 --> 00:08:54,454
Where have you been all this time, Heidi?

182
00:08:54,454 --> 00:08:56,454
On a hill.

183
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:00,454
There, a squirrel.

184
00:09:00,454 --> 00:09:03,454
Squirrels are also in our mountains.

185
00:09:03,454 --> 00:09:05,454
Exciting.

186
00:09:07,454 --> 00:09:09,454
Hurry up, but don't run into a tree.

187
00:09:09,454 --> 00:09:11,454
I'm trying.

188
00:09:17,024 --> 00:09:20,024
Where did it hide? I can't see it anymore.

189
00:09:20,024 --> 00:09:22,024
Up there on the big branch, look!

190
00:09:24,024 --> 00:09:26,024
Come on, little squirrel, come!

191
00:09:31,024 --> 00:09:32,024
Bravo!

192
00:09:33,024 --> 00:09:36,024
Clara! Heidi!

193
00:09:37,024 --> 00:09:39,024
Where are you children?

194
00:09:39,024 --> 00:09:41,952
Heidi! Clara!

195
00:09:41,952 --> 00:09:43,952
Come on, let's hide!

196
00:09:43,952 --> 00:09:45,952
Quiet!

197
00:09:45,952 --> 00:09:47,952
Kids!

198
00:09:47,952 --> 00:09:49,952
Little children!

199
00:09:49,952 --> 00:09:51,952
Where are you?

200
00:09:57,952 --> 00:09:59,952
Little children!

201
00:09:59,952 --> 00:10:01,952
Clara!

202
00:10:01,952 --> 00:10:03,952
Heidi!

203
00:10:03,952 --> 00:10:05,952
We have to go on, or they'll find us!

204
00:10:05,952 --> 00:10:07,952
Quiet!

205
00:10:07,952 --> 00:10:09,952
Oh, where did the children go?

206
00:10:09,952 --> 00:10:11,952
They were just here somewhere.

207
00:10:12,032 --> 00:10:13,032
Hello!

208
00:10:15,032 --> 00:10:16,032
Heidi!

209
00:10:17,032 --> 00:10:18,032
Clara!

210
00:10:18,032 --> 00:10:19,032
Look at you!

211
00:10:19,032 --> 00:10:20,032
Cuckoo!

212
00:10:21,472 --> 00:10:23,272
The earthworm has hidden her.

213
00:10:23,272 --> 00:10:24,972
The poor children have disappeared.

214
00:10:24,972 --> 00:10:27,472
How can I help it, Miss Rottenmeier?

215
00:10:27,472 --> 00:10:29,472
The poor little ones.

216
00:10:34,472 --> 00:10:36,224
That's too bad for me.

217
00:10:36,224 --> 00:10:39,224
I can never forgive myself for what has to happen.

218
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:46,224
What are you going to do? And where are you going to find food?

219
00:10:48,896 --> 00:10:55,896
Grandmother, there we are. Please don't cry.

220
00:11:01,896 --> 00:11:04,896
Edge, you fell in. I'm smarter.

221
00:11:04,896 --> 00:11:06,896
She did something to us.

222
00:11:06,896 --> 00:11:09,896
You're mean, Grandmother. I thought you were crying.

223
00:11:09,896 --> 00:11:12,896
Why am I mean? You two also wanted to put me in.

224
00:11:12,896 --> 00:11:14,896
Or is that not true?

225
00:11:18,896 --> 00:11:21,896
I don't know.

226
00:11:22,144 --> 00:11:24,144
I'd like to go for a ride.

227
00:11:24,972 --> 00:11:27,432
Let's go.

228
00:11:30,732 --> 00:11:32,372
Hello.

229
00:11:32,812 --> 00:11:34,212
Hello.

230
00:11:39,212 --> 00:11:43,172
John had to hurry to pick us up.

231
00:11:49,952 --> 00:11:51,212
Heidi, over there.

232
00:11:51,392 --> 00:11:52,532
Where?

233
00:11:52,812 --> 00:11:54,732
There are cows.

234
00:11:54,972 --> 00:11:56,972
Come in!

235
00:12:02,242 --> 00:12:05,242
And over there are even they.

236
00:12:07,242 --> 00:12:09,242
Do they look like yours?

237
00:12:09,242 --> 00:12:11,242
Yes, exactly the same.

238
00:12:15,242 --> 00:12:18,242
Grandmother, may I go to them?

239
00:12:32,242 --> 00:12:34,242
Yes, of course.

240
00:12:38,562 --> 00:12:41,962
I've never seen Heidi so happy before, Grandmother.

241
00:12:41,962 --> 00:12:44,962
Do you want to stand still? Stay here!

242
00:12:46,362 --> 00:12:49,162
Oh, Sebastian, please prepare tea and cake for us.

243
00:12:49,162 --> 00:12:49,962
Right away.

244
00:12:49,962 --> 00:12:51,962
I hate you, I hate you, I hate you!

245
00:12:51,962 --> 00:12:53,562
What are you doing with my goat?

246
00:12:53,562 --> 00:12:56,562
Don't chase my goat around like that, it shouldn't lose weight.

247
00:12:56,562 --> 00:12:58,562
We just played a little bit.

248
00:12:58,568 --> 00:13:01,768
If you want to play, then buy a parrot, but leave my goat alone.

249
00:13:01,768 --> 00:13:04,668
The child didn't mean it badly, but may I ask you something?

250
00:13:04,668 --> 00:13:08,168
Would you give the two children a sip of goat's milk afterwards?

251
00:13:08,168 --> 00:13:08,868
Me?

252
00:13:08,868 --> 00:13:13,168
Of course, you shouldn't do that for free, but our Clara has never drunk goat's
milk before.

253
00:13:13,168 --> 00:13:15,668
From me, if you really want to.

254
00:13:15,668 --> 00:13:17,068
A gold piece.

255
00:13:17,068 --> 00:13:19,668
You could take the goat with you to one of them.

256
00:13:21,468 --> 00:13:22,868
That's unbelievable.

257
00:13:22,868 --> 00:13:24,868
There's actually milk coming out of it.

258
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:30,490
Gail, you're amazed. You've never seen that before.

259
00:13:30,490 --> 00:13:32,490
May I? I'd like to milk her.

260
00:13:32,490 --> 00:13:34,490
You couldn't do that.

261
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:36,490
I think I can.

262
00:13:40,898 --> 00:13:42,898
Well, the world hasn't seen that yet.

263
00:13:42,898 --> 00:13:45,898
You even do that better than me, little one.

264
00:13:45,898 --> 00:13:47,898
That's hard to believe.

265
00:13:49,898 --> 00:13:53,898
Heidi, how can you do that? Just as well as the farmer's wife.

266
00:13:55,310 --> 00:13:57,310
Huh?

267
00:14:27,618 --> 00:14:29,618
I told you, eating is boring.

268
00:14:31,618 --> 00:14:34,618
You actually ate more this afternoon than Heidi.

269
00:14:34,618 --> 00:14:37,618
But I've never been as hungry as I am today.

270
00:14:37,618 --> 00:14:38,618
Yes, I know.

271
00:14:38,618 --> 00:14:43,618
Fresh air and sunshine even make a beep as if you were hungry like a bear.

272
00:14:47,618 --> 00:14:48,618
It tastes so good.

273
00:14:48,618 --> 00:14:52,618
HAPPY HALLOWEEN

274
00:14:52,618 --> 00:14:56,618
High on the yellow hill

275
00:14:56,618 --> 00:14:59,618
I sit at my brother-in-law's.

276
00:15:00,164 --> 00:15:03,164
Where did the fox go?

277
00:15:03,216 --> 00:15:08,216
The fox went to the grave, the sun glistens in a funny way.

